	* libslparse/parser.yxx 1.9:
		Allow empty array specifiers only when declaring arguments to
		functions or shaders.

2003-06-16  jpgrad
	* render/ishaderexecenv.h 1.14:
		- This is a bit complicated:
		
		  CqShaderExecEnv has CqRefCount as a superclass.  However, instances of
		  CqShaderExecEnv are often passed around as IqShaderExecEnv pointers.
		  Now, if we want to use reference counting properly with CqShaderExecEnv,
		  then we have to be able to call ADDREF() and RELEASEREF() with the
		  IqShaderExecEnv pointers.  Hence, I've added these two methods to
		  IqShaderExecEnv.

	* render/graphicsstate.cpp 1.7:
		- Added some more ADDREFs and RELEASEREFs.  These may not yet be balancing
		   perfectly (figuring out where they should go is complicated!), but are
		   holding up to testing.

	* libshadervm/shadervm.cpp 1.33:
		- Only use dynamic allocation for CqRefCount-derived classes.  Static
		   allocation is bad because it violates the contract for CqRefCount which
		   says that when RELEASEREF() is called for the last time then the
		   instance may be deleted.

	* render/options.h 1.28:
		- The CqOptions::ClearOptions() method shouldn't just call clear() on the
		   list of options, it should also call RELEASEREF() on each option to
		   decrement the reference count and allow the options (which are instances
		   of CqNamedParameterList*) to be deleted if necessary.

	* render/imagers.cpp 1.22:
		- Don't delete m_pShaderExecEnv directly, since it's a CqRefCount-derived
		  class.  Use RELEASEREF() instead.

	* libshaderexecenv/shaderexecenv.h 1.21:
		- Now that IqShaderExecEnv has pure virtual AddRef() and Release() methods,
		   these have to be defined in CqShaderExecEnv.  These implementations
		   simply call their CqRefCount equivalents.

	* render/attributes.h 1.25:
	* render/csgtree.h 1.11:
	* render/graphicsstate.h 1.7:
	* render/kdtree.h 1.2:
	* render/lights.h 1.18:
	* render/micropolygon.h 1.40:
	* render/subdivision2.h 1.21:
	* render/surface.h 1.48:
		- Added more className() debugging methods to these CqRefCount-derived
		   classes.

	* render/renderer.cpp 1.69:
	* render/renderer.h 1.41:
		- Set up the default transform and attributes so that these objects are
		   treated as CqRefCount sub-classes (which they are), and so use
		   RELEASEREF() to delete them rather than just calling delete().
		
		- Made the default options a member variable of CqRenderer.
		   Rationale:
		   1. Previously, the default options were only ever accessed via the
		       global instance of the CqRenderer class (this is also still the
		       case).
		   2. According to The RenderMan Companion, the RiOption() function may
		       not be called outside of the RiBegin() ... RiEnd() block, which is
		       the lifetime of the global CqRenderer instance.  Hence, the
		       default options may safely be instantiated when CqRenderer is
		       instantiated.
		   3. This helps when debugging reference counting issues! :-)

	* render/lights.cpp 1.23:
	* render/micropolygon.cpp 1.83:
		- Don't delete instances of IqShaderExecEnv directly.  Use RELEASEREF()
		   instead.

	* render/imagebuffer.cpp 1.116:
		- Make sure that a reference is held on a micropolygon grid while it is
		   being shaded.

	* libaqsistypes/refcount.cpp 1.5:
	* libaqsistypes/refcount.h 1.10:
		- Added some code to flag warnings when reference count instances are
		   deleted rather than released (via RELEASEREF).

2003-06-16  pgregory
	* slpp/libslpp.dsp 1.1:
		New project to build slpp as a link library.

2003-06-15  pgregory
	* aqsl/Makefile.am 1.18:
	* slpp/Makefile.am 1.3:
		Make library version of slpp work with Posix.

	* Renderer.dsw 1.70:
	* aqsl/aqslcomp.cpp 1.13:
