2003-06-12  jpgrad
	* libaqsistypes/Makefile.am 1.16:
	* libaqsistypes/refcount.cpp 1.1:
	* libaqsistypes/refcount.h 1.4:
	* libshaderexecenv/shaderexecenv.cpp 1.13:
	* render/attributes.h 1.24:
	* render/bucket.cpp 1.15:
	* render/csgtree.cpp 1.10:
	* render/csgtree.h 1.10:
	* render/curves.cpp 1.14:
	* render/genpoly.cpp 1.6:
	* render/genpoly.h 1.6:
	* render/graphicsstate.cpp 1.6:
	* render/iattributes.h 1.5:
	* render/imagebuffer.cpp 1.113:
	* render/imagebuffer.h 1.37:
	* render/imagers.cpp 1.21:
	* render/itransform.h 1.4:
	* render/lights.cpp 1.22:
	* render/micropolygon.cpp 1.82:
	* render/micropolygon.h 1.39:
	* render/nurbs.cpp 1.64:
	* render/options.cpp 1.31:
	* render/options.h 1.27:
	* render/patch.cpp 1.54:
	* render/points.cpp 1.22:
	* render/points.h 1.15:
	* render/polygon.cpp 1.40:
	* render/polygon.h 1.30:
	* render/procedural.cpp 1.7:
	* render/quadrics.h 1.21:
	* render/renderer.cpp 1.67:
	* render/ri.cpp 1.199:
	* render/subdivision2.cpp 1.27:
	* render/subdivision2.h 1.19:
	* render/surface.cpp 1.44:
	* render/surface.h 1.47:
	* render/teapot.cpp 1.15:
	* render/transform.h 1.9:
		- Added debugging information for reference counting.  Now, if Aqsis is
		  compiled with _DEBUG defined then all CqRefCount class instances (and
		  instances of derived classes) will be tracked to see where ADDREF() and
		  RELEASEREF() are called.  When rendering has finished, all un-released
		  CqRefCount objects are dumped, along with a history of their ADDREF()
		  and RELEASEREF() calls.
		
		  Note that ADDREF() and RELEASEREF() are macros which replace the AddRef()
		  and Release() method calls.  These macros take a pointer to a CqRefCount
		  class instance as an argument.
		
		  I stress that these changes are _only_ for debugging, and they aren't
		  fit, speed-wise, for an inclusion in a release build.  Ideally, don't
		  use any of this code for tracking statistics that we might want to
		  make available in a release build.

2003-06-12  pgregory
	* libaqsistypes/libaqsistypes.dsp 1.26:
	* libaqsistypes/refcount.cpp 1.2:
		Fix a couple of issues with new refcount tracking mechanism
		under Windows.

2003-06-11  pgregory
	* render/quadrics.cpp 1.51:
		Set the flag indicating the geometric normals have been
		processed.

	* render/libaqsis.def 1.7:
		Remove inline functions from .def file as they shouldn't be
		exported.

2003-06-09  pgregory
	* render/imagebuffer.cpp 1.112:
		Fix problem where diced bilinear patches which have been
		constructed from 3 point polygons (i.e. phantom 4th vertex case
		 tried to place u-polys in the previous bucket. Now
		automatically tries the current bucket to make sure any on the
		boundary are caught.

